        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 2:52PM AST by NWS San Juan PR</headline>
        <description>At 251 PM AST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lares. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Juncal, Maricao, and Lares.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
